{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ANRvbT9DmBQVE3as7SkSeN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class LoggerProducer implements Serializable {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→  @Produces\n    15→  public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n    16→    String loggerName = extractLoggerName(injectionPoint);\n    17→\n    18→    return Logger.getLogger(loggerName);\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  private String extractLoggerName(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n    22→    if (injectionPoint.getBean() == null) {\n    23→      return injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName();\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    if (injectionPoint.getBean().getName() == null) {\n    27→      return injectionPoint.getBean().getBeanClass().getName();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    return injectionPoint.getBean().getName();\n    31→  }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"89248b99-bcd8-4057-8d03-67fc3c6d72e0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FuuKR2VUKs5ULDtEb9Jg7v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Specification interface.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * <p>Use {@link AbstractSpecification} as base for creating specifications, and only the method\n     7→ * {@link #isSatisfiedBy(Object)} must be implemented.\n     8→ */\n     9→public interface Specification<T> {\n    10→\n    11→  /**\n    12→   * Check if {@code t} is satisfied by the specification.\n    13→   *\n    14→   * @param t Object to test.\n    15→   * @return {@code true} if {@code t} satisfies the specification.\n    16→   */\n    17→  boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t);\n    18→\n    19→  /**\n    20→   * Create a new specification that is the AND operation of {@code this} specification and another\n    21→   * specification.\n    22→   *\n    23→   * @param specification Specification to AND.\n    24→   * @return A new specification.\n    25→   */\n    26→  Specification<T> and(Specification<T> specification);\n    27→\n    28→  /**\n    29→   * Create a new specification that is the OR operation of {@code this} specification and another\n    30→   * specification.\n    31→   *\n    32→   * @param specification Specification to OR.\n    33→   * @return A new specification.\n    34→   */\n    35→  Specification<T> or(Specification<T> specification);\n    36→\n    37→  /**\n    38→   * Create a new specification that is the NOT operation of {@code this} specification.\n    39→   *\n    40→   * @param specification Specification to NOT.\n    41→   * @return A new specification.\n    42→   */\n    43→  Specification<T> not(Specification<T> specification);\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"93fd48f5-76c7-4927-a924-715a5e93cfa3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CYPokKUnSU2ZPnswLWpJyB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     4→public class DomainObjectUtils {\n     5→\n     6→  /** Prevent instantiation. */\n     7→  private DomainObjectUtils() {}\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param actual actual value\n    11→   * @param safe a null-safe value\n    12→   * @param <T> type\n    13→   * @return actual value, if it's not null, or safe value if the actual value is null.\n    14→   */\n    15→  public static <T> T nullSafe(T actual, T safe) {\n    16→    return actual == null ? safe : actual;\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"04152e86-cfde-4dab-b0f1-9bb6d0415787"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FKWrGwAP4AyQA6Nu78Q8ko","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * AND specification, used to create a new specification that is the AND of two other\n     5→ * specifications.\n     6→ */\n     7→public class AndSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n    10→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    11→\n    12→  /**\n    13→   * Create a new AND specification based on two other spec.\n    14→   *\n    15→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    16→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    17→   */\n    18→  public AndSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    19→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    20→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    26→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) && spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"cdb29d0a-f999-4b37-a9c9-ac514c93f88c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HAvUKAd4g2ofszjNiEunE5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Abstract base implementation of composite {@link Specification} with default implementations for\n     5→ * {@code and}, {@code or} and {@code not}.\n     6→ */\n     7→public abstract class AbstractSpecification<T> implements Specification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public abstract boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t);\n    12→\n    13→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public Specification<T> and(Specification<T> specification) {\n    16→    return new AndSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public Specification<T> or(Specification<T> specification) {\n    22→    return new OrSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public Specification<T> not(Specification<T> specification) {\n    28→    return new NotSpecification<>(specification);\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"30fe7e24-ae50-4cea-bd69-4f1a34387b3c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015NfeLprMiQ7aATXfNp1125","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * OR specification, used to create a new specification that is the OR of two other specifications.\n     5→ */\n     6→public class OrSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     7→\n     8→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    10→\n    11→  /**\n    12→   * Create a new OR specification based on two other spec.\n    13→   *\n    14→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    15→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    16→   */\n    17→  public OrSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    18→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    19→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    25→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) || spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"cc70f352-9ff9-41c5-b021-04bfff50b873"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HoamVbsU9MwyjRUJueh3Hh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/** NOT decorator, used to create a new specifcation that is the inverse (NOT) of the given spec. */\n     4→public class NotSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     5→\n     6→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     7→\n     8→  /**\n     9→   * Create a new NOT specification based on another spec.\n    10→   *\n    11→   * @param spec1 Specification instance to not.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public NotSpecification(Specification<T> spec1) {\n    14→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    20→    return !spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"4bf3c132-40a5-49d5-96e2-7f8f2b74318f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015pMJSasdpxoHc8XzjwWfmU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n     6→\n     7→public interface RoutingService {\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param routeSpecification Route specification\n    11→   * @return A list of itineraries that satisfy the specification. May be an empty list if no route\n    12→   *     is found.\n    13→   */\n    14→  List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification);\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"aaecf07a-ffdd-479e-bfe7-63814dc884be"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QCQH2i9dDmNp2XF6o1LaRP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\n     4→import java.util.concurrent.Executors;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.jms.ConnectionFactory;\n    11→import jakarta.jms.JMSConsumer;\n    12→import jakarta.jms.JMSContext;\n    13→import jakarta.jms.JMSException;\n    14→import jakarta.jms.Message;\n    15→import jakarta.jms.TextMessage;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    18→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    19→import io.quarkus.runtime.ShutdownEvent;\n    20→import io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * Consumes JMS messages and delegates notification of misdirected cargo to the tracking service.\n    24→ *\n    25→ * <p>\n    26→ * This is a programmatic hook into the JMS infrastructure to make cargo inspection message-driven.\n    27→ */\n    28→@ApplicationScoped\n    29→public class CargoHandledConsumer implements Runnable {\n    30→\n    31→  @Inject\n    32→  private Logger logger;\n    33→\n    34→  @Inject\n    35→  private ConnectionFactory connectionFactory;\n    36→\n    37→  @Inject\n    38→  private CargoInspectionService cargoInspectionService;\n    39→\n    40→  @ConfigProperty(name = \"app.jms.CargoHandledQueue\", defaultValue = \"CargoHandledQueue\")\n    41→  private String cargoHandledQueue;\n    42→\n    43→  private final ExecutorService scheduler = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();\n    44→\n    45→  public void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) {\n    46→    scheduler.submit(this);\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public void onStop(@Observes ShutdownEvent ev) {\n    50→    scheduler.shutdown();\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @Override\n    54→  public void run() {\n    55→    try (JMSContext context = connectionFactory.createContext(JMSContext.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE)) {\n    56→      JMSConsumer consumer = context.createConsumer(context.createQueue(cargoHandledQueue));\n    57→      while (true) {\n    58→        Message message = consumer.receive();\n    59→        TextMessage textMessage = (TextMessage) message;\n    60→        String trackingIdString = textMessage.getText();\n    61→\n    62→        cargoInspectionService.inspectCargo(new TrackingId(trackingIdString));\n    63→      }\n    64→    } catch (JMSException e) {\n    65→      logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error procesing JMS message\", e);\n    66→    }\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"46425797-6efd-4ab6-811d-98e4ef59cbcc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EosEFpf9jUh6CpE21YbnkA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\n     4→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\n     5→import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n     6→\n     7→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n     8→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    10→\n    11→@Qualifier\n    12→@Retention(RUNTIME)\n    13→@Target({FIELD, PARAMETER})\n    14→public @interface CargoUpdated {\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"75d5d4f5-0620-444d-bce4-68229cfc0d1d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019VojurxcRPrjbs7L9WfNrh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\n     4→import java.util.concurrent.Executors;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n     8→import io.quarkus.runtime.ShutdownEvent;\n     9→import io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent;\n    10→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    11→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.jms.ConnectionFactory;\n    14→import jakarta.jms.JMSConsumer;\n    15→import jakarta.jms.JMSContext;\n    16→import jakarta.jms.JMSException;\n    17→import jakarta.jms.Message;\n    18→\n    19→@ApplicationScoped\n    20→public class DeliveredCargoConsumer implements Runnable {\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject\n    23→  private Logger logger;\n    24→\n    25→  @Inject\n    26→  private ConnectionFactory connectionFactory;\n    27→\n    28→  @ConfigProperty(name = \"app.jms.DeliveredCargoQueue\", defaultValue = \"DeliveredCargoQueue\")\n    29→  private String deliveredCargoQueue;\n    30→\n    31→  private final ExecutorService scheduler = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();\n    32→\n    33→  public void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) {\n    34→    scheduler.submit(this);\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public void onStop(@Observes ShutdownEvent ev) {\n    38→    scheduler.shutdown();\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  @Override\n    42→  public void run() {\n    43→    try (JMSContext context = connectionFactory.createContext(JMSContext.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE)) {\n    44→      JMSConsumer consumer = context.createConsumer(context.createQueue(deliveredCargoQueue));\n    45→      while (true) {\n    46→        Message message = consumer.receive();\n    47→        logger.log(\n    48→            Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} delivered.\", message.getBody(String.class));\n    49→      }\n    50→    } catch (JMSException ex) {\n    51→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Error processing message.\", ex);\n    52→    }\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→}\n    56→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013c7ake6v2wL7dCozJG8CdA","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"73e94fef-b9ed-439e-b20d-4495f46ca09a"}
