{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011g943usFtyzUo3H7yJ37RP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * At the moment, coordinates are effectively a shared DTO in the interface layer. It may be\n     5→ * converted to a domain level concern at some point. *\n     6→ */\n     7→public class Coordinates {\n     8→\n     9→  private final double latitude;\n    10→  private final double longitude;\n    11→\n    12→  public Coordinates(double latitude, double longitude) {\n    13→    this.latitude = latitude;\n    14→    this.longitude = longitude;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public double getLatitude() {\n    18→    return latitude;\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public double getLongitude() {\n    22→    return longitude;\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"d5873e94-6ea6-4954-a47f-47c4839525c5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GKJ3aYXUx7DdegufJkBpBk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location.UNKNOWN;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.CHICAGO;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.DALLAS;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HAMBURG;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HANGZOU;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HELSINKI;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HONGKONG;\n    11→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.MELBOURNE;\n    12→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.NEWYORK;\n    13→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM;\n    14→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.SHANGHAI;\n    15→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM;\n    16→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.TOKYO;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collections;\n    19→import java.util.HashMap;\n    20→import java.util.Map;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * At the moment, coordinates are produced by a simple factory. It may be converted to a repository\n    26→ * if coordinates become a domain layer concern.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class CoordinatesFactory {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final Map<String, Coordinates> COORDINATES_MAP;\n    31→\n    32→  private CoordinatesFactory() {\n    33→    /* Prevent instantiation. */\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public static Coordinates find(Location location) {\n    37→    return find(location.getUnLocode());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public static Coordinates find(UnLocode unLocode) {\n    41→    return find(unLocode.getIdString());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public static Coordinates find(String unLocode) {\n    45→    return COORDINATES_MAP.get(unLocode);\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  static {\n    49→    Map<String, Coordinates> map = new HashMap<>();\n    50→\n    51→    // TODO [Clean Code] See if there is a service to get the latitude/longitude data from.\n    52→    map.put(HONGKONG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(22, 114));\n    53→    map.put(MELBOURNE.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-38, 145));\n    54→    map.put(STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(59, 18));\n    55→    map.put(HELSINKI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(60, 25));\n    56→    map.put(CHICAGO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(42, -88));\n    57→    map.put(TOKYO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(36, 140));\n    58→    map.put(HAMBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(54, 10));\n    59→    map.put(SHANGHAI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(31, 121));\n    60→    map.put(ROTTERDAM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(52, 5));\n    61→    map.put(GOTHENBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(58, 12));\n    62→    map.put(HANGZOU.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(30, 120));\n    63→    map.put(NEWYORK.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(41, -74));\n    64→    map.put(DALLAS.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(33, -97));\n    65→    map.put(UNKNOWN.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-90, 0)); // The South Pole.\n    66→\n    67→    COORDINATES_MAP = Collections.unmodifiableMap(map);\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"bbcd3510-9f63-4b38-aee6-c50f5e46d3fd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019MsyGQrDigGyHX7ZRu98Xt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collections;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.Random;\n     9→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    11→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n    14→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    19→import org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\n    20→\n    21→@ApplicationScoped\n    22→@Transactional\n    23→@Path(\"/graph-traversal\")\n    24→public class GraphTraversalService {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long ONE_MIN_MS = 1000 * 60;\n    27→  private static final long ONE_DAY_MS = ONE_MIN_MS * 60 * 24;\n    28→  private static final String UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE =\n    29→      \"UN location code value must be five characters long, \"\n    30→          + \"the first two must be alphabetic and \"\n    31→          + \"the last three must be alphanumeric (excluding 0 and 1).\";\n    32→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    33→  @Inject\n    34→  private GraphDao dao;\n    35→\n    36→  @GET\n    37→  @Path(\"/shortest-path\")\n    38→  @Produces({\"application/json\", \"application/xml; qs=.75\"})\n    39→  public TransitPaths findShortestPath(\n    40→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing origin UN location code.\") @Pattern(\n    41→          regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\",\n    42→          message = \"Origin \"\n    43→              + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE) @QueryParam(\"origin\") String originUnLocode,\n    44→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing destination UN location code.\") @Pattern(\n    45→          regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\",\n    46→          message = \"Destination \"\n    47→              + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE) @QueryParam(\"destination\") String destinationUnLocode,\n    48→      // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    49→      @Size(min = 8, max = 8,\n    50→          message = \"Deadline value must be eight characters long.\") @QueryParam(\"deadline\") String deadline) {\n    51→\n    52→    List<String> allVertices = dao.listLocations();\n    53→    allVertices.remove(originUnLocode);\n    54→    allVertices.remove(destinationUnLocode);\n    55→\n    56→    int candidateCount = getRandomNumberOfCandidates();\n    57→    List<TransitPath> candidates = new ArrayList<>(candidateCount);\n    58→\n    59→    for (int i = 0; i < candidateCount; i++) {\n    60→      allVertices = getRandomChunkOfLocations(allVertices);\n    61→      List<TransitEdge> transitEdges = new ArrayList<>(allVertices.size() - 1);\n    62→      String fromUnLocode = originUnLocode;\n    63→      LocalDateTime date = LocalDateTime.now();\n    64→\n    65→      for (int j = 0; j <= allVertices.size(); ++j) {\n    66→        LocalDateTime fromDate = nextDate(date);\n    67→        LocalDateTime toDate = nextDate(fromDate);\n    68→        String toUnLocode = (j >= allVertices.size() ? destinationUnLocode : allVertices.get(j));\n    69→        transitEdges.add(\n    70→            new TransitEdge(\n    71→                dao.getVoyageNumber(fromUnLocode, toUnLocode),\n    72→                fromUnLocode,\n    73→                toUnLocode,\n    74→                fromDate,\n    75→                toDate));\n    76→        fromUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    77→        date = nextDate(toDate);\n    78→      }\n    79→      candidates.add(new TransitPath(transitEdges));\n    80→    }\n    81→    return new TransitPaths(candidates);\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  private LocalDateTime nextDate(LocalDateTime date) {\n    85→    return date.plus(ONE_DAY_MS + (random.nextInt(1000) - 500) * ONE_MIN_MS, ChronoUnit.MILLIS);\n    86→  }\n    87→\n    88→  private int getRandomNumberOfCandidates() {\n    89→    return 3 + random.nextInt(3);\n    90→  }\n    91→\n    92→  private List<String> getRandomChunkOfLocations(List<String> allLocations) {\n    93→    Collections.shuffle(allLocations);\n    94→    int total = allLocations.size();\n    95→    int chunk = total > 4 ? 1 + random.nextInt(5) : total;\n    96→    return allLocations.subList(0, chunk);\n    97→  }\n    98→}\n    99→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"47cff280-52e6-4147-9c96-98ee6efc1eb5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LeveSCbzQLs9QKEGQmDh5j","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     7→\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class TransitPath implements Serializable {\n    10→\n    11→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    12→\n    13→  private List<TransitEdge> transitEdges;\n    14→\n    15→  public TransitPath() {\n    16→    this.transitEdges = new ArrayList<>();\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public TransitPath(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n    20→    this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public List<TransitEdge> getTransitEdges() {\n    24→    return transitEdges;\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public void setTransitEdges(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n    28→    this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public String toString() {\n    33→    return \"TransitPath{\" + \"transitEdges=\" + transitEdges + '}';\n    34→  }\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"57a4a5d1-bf86-449e-8498-6c3f4eee5795"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HGxbAXzzeV249bsTBFWLpQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     7→\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class TransitPaths implements Serializable {\n    10→\n    11→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    12→\n    13→    private List<TransitPath> transitPaths;\n    14→\n    15→    public TransitPaths() {\n    16→        this.transitPaths = new ArrayList<>();\n    17→    }\n    18→\n    19→    public TransitPaths(List<TransitPath> transitPaths) {\n    20→        this.transitPaths = transitPaths;\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    public List<TransitPath> getTransitPaths() {\n    24→        return transitPaths;\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    public void setTransitPaths(List<TransitPath> transitPaths) {\n    28→        this.transitPaths = transitPaths;\n    29→    }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"e5c3fcfe-433e-4d13-8dd4-5c493bbfb7c7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QKAoduZ1gNUFQj9SHA2iX5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→\n     6→/** Represents an edge in a path through a graph, describing the route of a cargo. */\n     7→public class TransitEdge implements Serializable {\n     8→\n     9→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    10→\n    11→  private String voyageNumber;\n    12→  private String fromUnLocode;\n    13→  private String toUnLocode;\n    14→  private LocalDateTime fromDate;\n    15→  private LocalDateTime toDate;\n    16→\n    17→  public TransitEdge() {\n    18→    // Nothing to do.\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public TransitEdge(\n    22→      String voyageNumber,\n    23→      String fromUnLocode,\n    24→      String toUnLocode,\n    25→      LocalDateTime fromDate,\n    26→      LocalDateTime toDate) {\n    27→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    28→    this.fromUnLocode = fromUnLocode;\n    29→    this.toUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    30→    this.fromDate = fromDate;\n    31→    this.toDate = toDate;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    35→    return voyageNumber;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public void setVoyageNumber(String voyageNumber) {\n    39→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public String getFromUnLocode() {\n    43→    return fromUnLocode;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public void setFromUnLocode(String fromUnLocode) {\n    47→    this.fromUnLocode = fromUnLocode;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public String getToUnLocode() {\n    51→    return toUnLocode;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public void setToUnLocode(String toUnLocode) {\n    55→    this.toUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public LocalDateTime getFromDate() {\n    59→    return fromDate;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void setFromDate(LocalDateTime fromDate) {\n    63→    this.fromDate = fromDate;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public LocalDateTime getToDate() {\n    67→    return toDate;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public void setToDate(LocalDateTime toDate) {\n    71→    this.toDate = toDate;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  @Override\n    75→  public String toString() {\n    76→    return \"TransitEdge{\"\n    77→        + \"voyageNumber=\"\n    78→        + voyageNumber\n    79→        + \", fromUnLocode=\"\n    80→        + fromUnLocode\n    81→        + \", toUnLocode=\"\n    82→        + toUnLocode\n    83→        + \", fromDate=\"\n    84→        + fromDate\n    85→        + \", toDate=\"\n    86→        + toDate\n    87→        + '}';\n    88→  }\n    89→}\n    90→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"497f1013-4e91-4e7e-bae3-8faa08e49011"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WFsnXPxfbCAqEVdCGkbqzP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Random;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class GraphDao implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    16→\n    17→  public List<String> listLocations() {\n    18→    return new ArrayList<>(\n    19→        Arrays.asList(\n    20→            \"CNHKG\", \"AUMEL\", \"SESTO\", \"FIHEL\", \"USCHI\", \"JNTKO\", \"DEHAM\", \"CNSHA\", \"NLRTM\",\n    21→            \"SEGOT\", \"CNHGH\", \"USNYC\", \"USDAL\"));\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public String getVoyageNumber(String from, String to) {\n    25→    int i = random.nextInt(5);\n    26→\n    27→    switch (i) {\n    28→      case 0:\n    29→        return \"0100S\";\n    30→      case 1:\n    31→        return \"0200T\";\n    32→      case 2:\n    33→        return \"0300A\";\n    34→      case 3:\n    35→        return \"0301S\";\n    36→      default:\n    37→        return \"0400S\";\n    38→    }\n    39→  }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E1u8gYRBjYTGPDhDxgufJz","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"87d75824-98b6-4520-9970-697ac629d19b"}
