{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The conversation is summarized below:\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the conversation to capture all important details:\n\n1. **Initial User Request**: The user is an autonomous AI coding agent tasked with migrating a Java application from Quarkus to Spring Boot. The migration must be completed in a single execution without requesting additional input. Detailed checklist and constraints were provided including Docker isolation requirements, migration workflow, validation protocol, error handling, and output format requirements.\n\n2. **Phase 1 - Codebase Analysis**: \n   - Explored the directory structure at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output`\n   - Read pom.xml (Quarkus 3.30.5, Java 21)\n   - Read Dockerfile (Maven 3.9.12, ActiveMQ Artemis 2.31.2)\n   - Read application.properties (Quarkus-specific config)\n   - Read import.sql (single insert for ApplicationSettings)\n   - Globbed for all Java files (~100+ files), properties, XML, XHTML, SQL files\n   - Used Task agents to read all Java source files in three batches covering domain, infrastructure, and interfaces packages\n\n3. **Phase 2 - pom.xml Migration**:\n   - Rewrote pom.xml from Quarkus BOM to Spring Boot 3.4.3 parent\n   - Key dependencies: spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, spring-boot-starter-validation, spring-boot-starter-artemis, spring-boot-starter-batch, h2, commons-lang3, jackson-datatype-jsr310\n\n4. **Phase 3 - Main Application & Config**:\n   - Created CargoTrackerApplication.java with @SpringBootApplication and @EnableScheduling\n   - Rewrote application.properties with Spring Boot equivalents\n\n5. **Phase 4 - Infrastructure Layer Migration**:\n   - Rewrote 4 JPA repositories (JpaCargoRepository, JpaHandlingEventRepository, JpaLocationRepository, JpaVoyageRepository) from Panache to EntityManager-based\n   - Rewrote 6 JMS messaging files (JmsApplicationEvents, CargoHandledConsumer, DeliveredCargoConsumer, MisdirectedCargoConsumer, HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer, RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer) from Quarkus CDI+manual consumers to Spring JMS @JmsListener\n   - Created JmsConfig.java (new) with @EnableJms, JmsListenerContainerFactory, MessageConverter, JmsTemplate\n   - Rewrote LoggerProducer.java (placeholder)\n   - Rewrote CargoUpdated.java (marker annotation)\n   - Rewrote ExternalRoutingService.java (JAX-RS Client → RestTemplate)\n\n6. **Phase 5 - Application Layer Migration**:\n   - Rewrote DefaultBookingService.java, DefaultHandlingEventService.java, DefaultCargoInspectionService.java\n   - Rewrote HandlingEventFactory.java\n   - Rewrote SampleDataGenerator.java (@Startup → @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class))\n   - Rewrote InitLoader.java\n   - Rewrote RestConfiguration.java (placeholder)\n\n7. **Phase 6 - Interfaces Layer Migration**:\n   - Rewrote HandlingReportService.java (JAX-RS → Spring @RestController)\n   - Rewrote GraphTraversalService.java (JAX-RS → Spring @RestController)\n   - Rewrote GraphDao.java\n   - Rewrote RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java (JAX-RS SSE → Spring SseEmitter)\n   - Rewrote DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java\n   - Rewrote all assembler classes (CargoRouteDtoAssembler, CargoStatusDtoAssembler, LocationDtoAssembler, TrackingEventsDtoAssembler, ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler)\n\n8. **Current State**: The assistant was about to handle the remaining JSF web beans (Booking, Track, ListCargo, CargoDetails, ItinerarySelection, ChangeDestination, ChangeDestinationDialog, ChangeArrivalDeadline, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog, EventLogger), FacesConfiguration, batch processing files (UploadDirectoryScanner, EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, FileProcessorJobListener, LineParseExceptionListener), update the Dockerfile, create smoke tests, build, run, and test the application, and document everything in CHANGELOG.md.\n\nThe TODO list at the time of summary request shows:\n- Completed: Analyze, pom.xml, config, infrastructure, application layer, REST/SSE interfaces\n- In Progress: Remove JSF-specific code and add Spring MVC equivalents\n- Pending: Update Dockerfile, Generate smoke tests, Build/run/test, Fix errors, Document CHANGELOG.md\n\nKey patterns used in migration:\n- @ApplicationScoped → @Service/@Component/@Repository\n- @Inject → @Autowired\n- @ConfigProperty → @Value\n- jakarta.transaction.Transactional → org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional\n- @Observes StartupEvent → @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)\n- PanacheRepositoryBase → EntityManager-based repositories\n- JAX-RS (@Path, @GET, @POST) → Spring MVC (@RestController, @GetMapping, @PostMapping)\n- CDI Event → ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Manual JMS consumers (Runnable + ExecutorService) → @JmsListener\n- JAX-RS SSE → Spring SseEmitter\n\nNo compilation errors have been encountered yet since no build has been attempted.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user is an autonomous AI coding agent tasked with migrating a complete Java Cargo Tracker DDD application from **Quarkus** to **Spring Boot**. The migration must be completed in a single execution without requesting additional input. The application is located at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output`. \n   \n   Key requirements:\n   - Migrate all framework-specific dependencies, annotations, and patterns from Quarkus to Spring Boot\n   - Generate smoke tests to verify functionality\n   - Build as Docker image, run container, execute smoke tests\n   - Use `$SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME`, `$SCARF_IMAGE_TAG` env vars and `-p 0:8080` for Docker operations\n   - Document all actions in `CHANGELOG.md`\n   - Address any errors and iterate until the application builds, runs, and passes tests\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Quarkus → Spring Boot 3.4.3** framework migration\n   - **Java 21** target\n   - **DDD (Domain-Driven Design)** architecture with aggregates, repositories, services, value objects\n   - **CDI (@ApplicationScoped, @Inject, @Produces, @Observes) → Spring DI (@Service, @Component, @Repository, @Autowired, @EventListener)**\n   - **Quarkus Panache repositories → Spring EntityManager-based repositories**\n   - **JAX-RS (@Path, @GET, @POST, @QueryParam) → Spring MVC (@RestController, @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PostMapping, @RequestParam)**\n   - **MicroProfile Config (@ConfigProperty) → Spring @Value**\n   - **Quarkus JMS (manual consumers with ExecutorService) → Spring JMS (@JmsListener, JmsTemplate)**\n   - **JAX-RS SSE (SseBroadcaster, SseEventSink) → Spring SseEmitter**\n   - **CDI Events (Event<T>, @ObservesAsync) → Spring ApplicationEventPublisher**\n   - **JSF/PrimeFaces UI → Spring REST controllers** (JSF not supported in Spring Boot)\n   - **Jakarta Batch (JBeret) → Spring Batch**\n   - **Quarkus Scheduler (@Scheduled(every=\"2m\")) → Spring @Scheduled**\n   - **ActiveMQ Artemis** as JMS broker (AMQP in Quarkus → TCP/core protocol in Spring)\n   - **H2 file-based database**\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   **BUILD & CONFIG FILES:**\n\n   - **pom.xml** - Completely rewritten from Quarkus BOM to Spring Boot parent\n     - Spring Boot 3.4.3 parent, Java 21\n     - Dependencies: spring-boot-starter-web, data-jpa, validation, artemis, batch, h2, commons-lang3, jackson-datatype-jsr310, spring-boot-starter-test\n     ```xml\n     <parent>\n         <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n         <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>\n         <version>3.4.3</version>\n         <relativePath/>\n     </parent>\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/resources/application.properties** - Rewritten with Spring Boot property names\n     - `server.servlet.context-path=/cargo-tracker`\n     - `spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-data/cargo-tracker-database`\n     - `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop`\n     - `spring.artemis.broker-url=tcp://localhost:61616` (changed from amqp://localhost:5672)\n     - Custom app properties preserved: `app.jms.*` and `app.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl`\n     - `spring.batch.jdbc.initialize-schema=always`, `spring.batch.job.enabled=false`\n\n   - **Dockerfile** - NOT YET UPDATED (still references `mvn quarkus:run`)\n\n   **NEW FILES:**\n\n   - **src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/CargoTrackerApplication.java** - Spring Boot main class\n     ```java\n     @SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = {\"org.eclipse.cargotracker\", \"org.eclipse.pathfinder\"})\n     @EnableScheduling\n     public class CargoTrackerApplication {\n         public static void main(String[] args) {\n             SpringApplication.run(CargoTrackerApplication.class, args);\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/JmsConfig.java** - New Spring JMS configuration\n     ```java\n     @Configuration\n     @EnableJms\n     public class JmsConfig {\n         // JmsListenerContainerFactory, MappingJackson2MessageConverter, JmsTemplate beans\n     }\n     ```\n\n   **INFRASTRUCTURE LAYER (Rewritten):**\n\n   - **JpaCargoRepository.java** - Panache → EntityManager, @ApplicationScoped → @Repository, CDI Event → ApplicationEventPublisher, added `listAll()` method\n   - **JpaHandlingEventRepository.java** - Panache → EntityManager, @Repository\n   - **JpaLocationRepository.java** - Panache → EntityManager, @Repository, added `listAll()` method\n   - **JpaVoyageRepository.java** - Panache → EntityManager, @Repository, added `listAll()` method\n   - **JmsApplicationEvents.java** - @Service, JmsTemplate.convertAndSend() instead of JMSContext\n   - **CargoHandledConsumer.java** - @Component, @JmsListener instead of manual Runnable+ExecutorService\n   - **DeliveredCargoConsumer.java** - @Component, @JmsListener\n   - **MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java** - @Component, @JmsListener\n   - **HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java** - @Component, @JmsListener\n   - **RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java** - @Component, @JmsListener\n   - **ExternalRoutingService.java** - @Service, RestTemplate instead of JAX-RS Client\n   - **LoggerProducer.java** - Stripped to placeholder @Component\n   - **CargoUpdated.java** - Stripped to marker annotation (Spring uses ApplicationEventPublisher)\n\n   **APPLICATION LAYER (Rewritten):**\n\n   - **DefaultBookingService.java** - @Service, @Transactional (Spring), @Autowired, static Logger\n   - **DefaultHandlingEventService.java** - @Service, @Transactional(rollbackFor=...), @Autowired\n   - **DefaultCargoInspectionService.java** - @Service, @Transactional, @Autowired\n   - **HandlingEventFactory.java** - @Component, @Transactional(rollbackFor=...), @Autowired\n   - **SampleDataGenerator.java** - @Component, @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class) replaces @Startup+@PostConstruct+@UnlessBuildProfile\n   - **InitLoader.java** - @Service, @PersistenceContext EntityManager, Spring @Transactional\n   - **RestConfiguration.java** - Stripped to empty placeholder class\n\n   **INTERFACES LAYER (Rewritten):**\n\n   - **HandlingReportService.java** - @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/handling\"), @PostMapping, @RequestBody\n   - **GraphTraversalService.java** - @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/graph-traversal\"), @GetMapping, @RequestParam\n   - **GraphDao.java** - @Component\n   - **RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java** - @RestController, SseEmitter instead of JAX-RS SSE, @EventListener for cargo updates\n   - **DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java** - @Service, @Autowired\n   - **CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java** - @Component\n   - **CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java** - @Component\n   - **LocationDtoAssembler.java** - @Component\n   - **TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java** - @Component\n   - **ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java** - @Component (rewritten by sub-agent)\n\n   **DOMAIN LAYER (Unchanged):**\n   - All domain model files (Cargo, Delivery, Itinerary, Leg, HandlingEvent, Location, Voyage, etc.) use standard JPA annotations and remain compatible - no changes needed.\n\n   **NOT YET MODIFIED (JSF/Batch files still containing Quarkus code):**\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/Booking.java` - @FlowScoped(\"booking\"), JSF/PrimeFaces\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/Track.java` - @ViewScoped, JSF\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/ListCargo.java` - @RequestScoped, JSF\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/CargoDetails.java` - @RequestScoped, JSF\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/ItinerarySelection.java` - @ViewScoped, JSF\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/ChangeDestination.java` - @ViewScoped, JSF/PrimeFaces\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/ChangeDestinationDialog.java` - @SessionScoped, PrimeFaces\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/ChangeArrivalDeadline.java` - @ViewScoped, JSF\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java` - @SessionScoped, PrimeFaces\n   - `interfaces/handling/mobile/EventLogger.java` - @Named @ViewScoped, JSF/PrimeFaces, uses `io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort`\n   - `interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java` - @FacesConfig, CDI\n   - `interfaces/handling/file/UploadDirectoryScanner.java` - `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled`, Jakarta Batch\n   - `interfaces/handling/file/EventItemReader.java` - Jakarta Batch @Dependent\n   - `interfaces/handling/file/EventItemWriter.java` - Jakarta Batch @Dependent\n   - `interfaces/handling/file/FileProcessorJobListener.java` - Jakarta Batch @Dependent\n   - `interfaces/handling/file/LineParseExceptionListener.java` - Jakarta Batch @Dependent\n   - All XHTML files in META-INF/resources/ (JSF templates)\n   - `META-INF/faces-config.xml`\n   - `META-INF/web.xml`\n   - `META-INF/batch-jobs/EventFilesProcessorJob.xml`\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - No compilation or runtime errors have been encountered yet - no build has been attempted.\n   - The application has NOT yet been compiled, built as Docker image, or tested.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - **JSF/PrimeFaces incompatibility with Spring Boot**: Decision made to replace JSF web beans with Spring REST controllers, keeping the REST API layer functional. The JSF XHTML pages cannot work in Spring Boot.\n   - **Quarkus Panache → Standard JPA**: All Panache-specific methods (`find()` with named queries via Panache `Parameters`, `persist()`, `listAll()`, `getEntityManager()`) were replaced with standard `EntityManager` calls.\n   - **JMS consumer pattern**: Quarkus used manual Runnable+ExecutorService consumers with lifecycle events. Replaced with declarative Spring `@JmsListener` annotations.\n   - **CDI qualifiers and events**: `@CargoUpdated` CDI qualifier + `Event<Cargo>` replaced with Spring `ApplicationEventPublisher.publishEvent()` and `@EventListener`.\n   - **AMQP → Core protocol**: Artemis connection changed from `amqp://localhost:5672` to `tcp://localhost:61616` for Spring Boot Artemis starter compatibility.\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - **Message 1**: Full migration specification with detailed checklist, environment constraints, Docker isolation requirements, migration workflow (5 phases), validation protocol, error handling instructions, output format requirements, and final notes. Key: \"Begin migration now.\"\n   - **Message 2**: (System reminder about TodoWrite tool - not a user message)\n   - **Message 3**: (System reminder about TodoWrite tool - not a user message)\n\n7. Pending Tasks (from TODO list and migration checklist):\n   - **Remove/rewrite JSF-specific web beans** (Booking.java, Track.java, ListCargo.java, CargoDetails.java, ItinerarySelection.java, ChangeDestination.java, ChangeDestinationDialog.java, ChangeArrivalDeadline.java, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java, EventLogger.java, FacesConfiguration.java) - these still have Quarkus/JSF imports\n   - **Rewrite batch processing files** (UploadDirectoryScanner.java, EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, FileProcessorJobListener, LineParseExceptionListener) - still use Jakarta Batch and Quarkus scheduler annotations\n   - **Update Dockerfile** for Spring Boot (currently references `mvn quarkus:run`)\n   - **Generate smoke tests** (smoke.py or similar)\n   - **Build the Docker image** (`docker build -t $SCARF_IMAGE_TAG .`)\n   - **Run the container** and verify startup\n   - **Execute smoke tests** against the running container\n   - **Fix any compilation/runtime errors** iteratively\n   - **Create CHANGELOG.md** documenting all actions\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The assistant had just completed rewriting the interfaces layer (REST controllers, SSE, facade, assemblers) and was about to begin removing/rewriting JSF-specific code. The TODO list shows \"Remove JSF-specific code and add Spring MVC equivalents\" as `in_progress`. \n   \n   The assistant's last action before the summary request was updating the TODO list to reflect this status. The previous work completed all the assembler rewrites and the main REST endpoints. The next logical step is to handle the ~10 JSF web bean files that still contain Quarkus/JSF-specific imports (`@FlowScoped`, `@ViewScoped`, `@RequestScoped`, `@SessionScoped`, `FacesContext`, `PrimeFaces`, `io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort`, etc.) which will cause compilation failures.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   The immediate next step is to **remove or rewrite the JSF-specific web bean files** that still contain Quarkus/Jakarta Faces imports. These files are:\n   - `interfaces/booking/web/*.java` (9 files)\n   - `interfaces/handling/mobile/EventLogger.java`\n   - `interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java`\n   - `interfaces/handling/file/UploadDirectoryScanner.java` and other batch files\n   \n   These need to either be deleted (if functionality is covered by new REST controllers) or converted to simple Spring @Component/@Controller classes to compile. Then update the Dockerfile, attempt the first build, and iterate on errors.\n   \n   This directly continues the migration checklist item: \"Remove JSF-specific code and add Spring MVC equivalents\" which was marked as `in_progress` in the TODO list..\nPlease continue the conversation from where we left it off without asking the user any further questions. Continue with the last task that you were asked to work on."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"ff11835d-4a61-4ff1-9c28-ff35c207025b","isSynthetic":true}
