{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VGZAh5fgofTyW689fX4ugx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have successfully read the contents of all 11 Java files you requested. The files are from the `org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces` package and are related to different web and mobile interfaces for a cargo tracking application. \n\nHere's a brief overview of the files:\n\n1. `Booking.java`: Handles the booking of new cargo, allowing users to select origin, destination, and arrival deadline.\n2. `Track.java`: Manages tracking cargo by tracking ID in the admin interface.\n3. `ListCargo.java`: Provides lists of cargo with different statuses (not routed, routed unclaimed, claimed).\n4. `CargoDetails.java`: Loads and displays details for a specific cargo.\n5. `ItinerarySelection.java`: Allows selection of routes for a cargo.\n6. `ChangeDestination.java`: Enables changing the destination of a cargo.\n7. `ChangeDestinationDialog.java`: Handles the dialog for changing cargo destination.\n8. `ChangeArrivalDeadline.java`: Allows changing the arrival deadline for a cargo.\n9. `ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java`: Manages the dialog for changing arrival deadline.\n10. `EventLogger.java`: A mobile interface for logging handling events for cargo.\n11. `FacesConfiguration.java`: A simple Jakarta Faces configuration class.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific file or provide more details about the code?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"b11d059c-d454-4835-b79d-78aa1c9d765e"}
