{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014HCB4SxeebqGUz6CUPmHoF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.File;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→\n     8→public class EventFilesCheckpoint implements Serializable {\n     9→\n    10→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→  private List<File> files = new LinkedList<>();\n    13→  private int fileIndex = 0;\n    14→  private long filePointer = 0;\n    15→\n    16→  public void setFiles(List<File> files) {\n    17→    this.files = files;\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  public long getFilePointer() {\n    21→    return filePointer;\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public void setFilePointer(long filePointer) {\n    25→    this.filePointer = filePointer;\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  public File currentFile() {\n    29→    if (files.size() > fileIndex) {\n    30→      return files.get(fileIndex);\n    31→    } else {\n    32→      return null;\n    33→    }\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public File nextFile() {\n    37→    filePointer = 0;\n    38→\n    39→    if (files.size() > ++fileIndex) {\n    40→      return files.get(fileIndex);\n    41→    } else {\n    42→      return null;\n    43→    }\n    44→  }\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"1bda4ae5-6183-4095-a5f7-33a7a885962c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019F4FxGPXtub51BSVbW5jKp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→public class EventLineParseException extends RuntimeException {\n     4→\n     5→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     6→\n     7→  private final String line;\n     8→\n     9→  public EventLineParseException(String message, Throwable cause, String line) {\n    10→    super(message, cause);\n    11→    this.line = line;\n    12→  }\n    13→\n    14→  public EventLineParseException(String message, String line) {\n    15→    super(message);\n    16→    this.line = line;\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public String getLine() {\n    20→    return line;\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"197f67a6-1d19-4273-aa43-ff3e6b1bec26"}
