er.java\n-rw-r-----. 1 bmcginn users 1390 Mar 14 12:56 /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/UploadDirectoryScanner.java","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015ff4Yvbb2Pr651kbQSESgR","session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"45fcedd7-398c-40c9-85b6-998f1020ec2d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TCYDGaeD7sR1hEzg32GLNY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! The migration is complete. Let me create a summary document of what was done:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated the JSF web bean files to a single Spring REST controller as part of the Quarkus-to-Spring-Boot migration of the Cargo Tracker DDD application.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**Created:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/BookingController.java`\n\n**Deleted (9 old JSF bean files):**\n1. `Booking.java` - JSF @FlowScoped bean for cargo booking\n2. `Track.java` - JSF @ViewScoped bean for cargo tracking\n3. `ListCargo.java` - JSF @RequestScoped bean for listing cargos\n4. `CargoDetails.java` - JSF @RequestScoped bean for cargo details\n5. `ItinerarySelection.java` - JSF @ViewScoped bean for route selection\n6. `ChangeDestination.java` - JSF @ViewScoped bean for changing destination\n7. `ChangeDestinationDialog.java` - JSF @SessionScoped bean for destination dialog\n8. `ChangeArrivalDeadline.java` - JSF @ViewScoped bean for changing deadline\n9. `ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java` - JSF @SessionScoped bean for deadline dialog\n\n### New BookingController REST Endpoints\n\nThe new `BookingController` is a Spring `@RestController` that consolidates all booking-related functionality under the base path `/rest/booking`. It provides the following REST endpoints:\n\n#### Location Management\n- `GET /rest/booking/locations` - Lists all shipping locations\n\n#### Cargo Booking\n- `POST /rest/booking/cargo` - Books a new cargo (params: originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline)\n\n#### Cargo Listing & Details\n- `GET /rest/booking/cargos` - Lists all cargos grouped by status (notRouted, routedUnclaimed, claimed)\n- `GET /rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}` - Retrieves cargo routing details\n\n#### Cargo Tracking\n- `GET /rest/booking/tracking/ids` - Lists all tracking IDs\n- `GET /rest/booking/tracking/{trackingId}` - Retrieves cargo tracking status\n\n#### Route Management\n- `GET /rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/routes` - Requests possible routes for a cargo\n- `POST /rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/assign-route` - Assigns a selected route to a cargo\n\n#### Cargo Modifications\n- `PUT /rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/destination` - Changes cargo destination (param: destinationUnlocode)\n- `PUT /rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/deadline` - Changes cargo arrival deadline (param: deadline)\n\n### Key Features of the Migration\n\n1. **Consolidated Architecture**: All JSF beans have been merged into a single, cohesive REST controller, eliminating redundancy and simplifying the API structure.\n\n2. **RESTful Design**: Uses proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT) and follows REST conventions with path variables and request parameters.\n\n3. **Spring Boot Native**: Uses Spring annotations (`@RestController`, `@RequestMapping`, `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`, `@PutMapping`, `@PathVariable`, `@RequestParam`, `@RequestBody`, `@Autowired`).\n\n4. **Proper Date Handling**: Uses `@DateTimeFormat(iso = DateTimeFormat.ISO.DATE)` for LocalDate parameters.\n\n5. **Error Handling**: Includes validation (e.g., ensuring origin and destination are not the same) with proper HTTP status codes.\n\n6. **Complete Documentation**: Extensive JavaDoc comments documenting each endpoint and mapping it back to the original JSF bean method it replaces.\n\n7. **Clean Separation**: Maintains separation from the domain layer by operating through the `BookingServiceFacade` interface, preserving the DDD architecture.\n\nThe migration is complete and the booking interface is now fully Spring Boot compatible with a modern REST API architecture."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"c3a8aacd-bfc1-48d0-8d54-cf4ca5f05cda"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015ff4Yvbb2Pr651kbQSESgR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All files have been successfully migrated. Let me create a summary of the changes:\n\n## Quarkus-to-Spring-Boot Batch Processing Migration Complete\n\nI have successfully migrated all batch processing files from Jakarta Batch API (JBeret/Quarkus) to Spring Batch. Here's what was done:\n\n### Files Converted (5 files rewritten):\n\n1. **UploadDirectoryScanner.java** \n   - Path: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/UploadDirectoryScanner.java`\n   - Changed from: `@ApplicationScoped`, `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled`, `jakarta.batch.operations.JobOperator`\n   - Changed to: `@Component`, `@Scheduled(fixedRate = 120000)`, Spring `JobLauncher` and `Job`\n\n2. **EventItemReader.java**\n   - Path: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/EventItemReader.java`\n   - Changed from: `extends AbstractItemReader` (Jakarta Batch)\n   - Changed to: `implements ItemReader<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt>` (Spring Batch)\n   - Replaced checkpoint-based file tracking with stateful instance variables\n\n3. **EventItemWriter.java**\n   - Path: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/EventItemWriter.java`\n   - Changed from: `extends AbstractItemWriter` with `writeItems(List<Object>)`\n   - Changed to: `implements ItemWriter<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt>` with `write(Chunk<?>)`\n\n4. **FileProcessorJobListener.java**\n   - Path: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/FileProcessorJobListener.java`\n   - Changed from: `implements JobListener` (Jakarta Batch)\n   - Changed to: `implements JobExecutionListener` (Spring Batch)\n   - Updated method signatures to accept `JobExecution` parameter\n\n5. **LineParseExceptionListener.java**\n   - Path: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/LineParseExceptionListener.java`\n   - Changed from: `implements SkipReadListener` (Jakarta Batch)\n   - Changed to: `implements SkipListener<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt, HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt>` (Spring Batch)\n   - Updated method signatures for Spring Batch skip listener interface\n\n### File Created (1 new file):\n\n6. **BatchJobConfig.java**\n   - Path: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/BatchJobConfig.java`\n   - New Spring `@Configuration` class that defines:\n     - `eventFilesProcessorJob` bean with job listener\n     - `eventProcessingStep` bean with chunk-oriented processing (chunk size: 10)\n     - Fault tolerance configuration with skip support for `EventLineParseException` (skip limit: 100)\n\n### Files Deleted (3 XML files):\n\n1. `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/batch-jobs/EventFilesProcessorJob.xml` - Jakarta Batch XML job descriptor (no longer needed)\n2. `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/faces-config.xml` - JSF configuration (not needed in Spring Boot)\n3. `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/web.xml` - JSF web descriptor (not needed in Spring Boot)\n\n### Key Migration Changes:\n\n- **Dependency Injection**: Changed from CDI (`@Inject`, `@Named`, `@Dependent`) to Spring (`@Autowired`, `@Component`)\n- **Scheduling**: Migrated from Quarkus `@Scheduled(every = \"2m\")` to Spring `@Scheduled(fixedRate = 120000)`\n- **Job Execution**: Replaced Jakarta Batch `JobOperator.start()` with Spring Batch `JobLauncher.run()`\n- **Configuration**: Moved from XML-based job definition to Java-based `@Configuration` with builder pattern\n- **Batch API**: All Jakarta Batch API imports replaced with Spring Batch equivalents\n- **Transaction Management**: Spring's `@Transactional` annotation retained for transactional write operations\n\nThe migration is complete and the batch processing system is now fully Spring Boot compatible!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"83a6961f-f58e-4d4b-8ccd-5d70d8c77eea"}
