{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The conversation is summarized below:\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the conversation to capture all important details:\n\n**Context from Previous Session Summary:**\nThe conversation is a continuation of a Quarkus-to-Spring Boot migration of a Cargo Tracker DDD application. The previous session had completed:\n1. Analysis of the codebase\n2. pom.xml migration (Quarkus BOM → Spring Boot 3.4.3 parent)\n3. Main application class creation (CargoTrackerApplication.java)\n4. application.properties migration\n5. Infrastructure layer (repositories, messaging, JMS config)\n6. Application layer (services, data loader)\n7. Interfaces layer (REST endpoints, SSE, facade, assemblers)\n\nThe previous session left off with \"Remove JSF-specific code and add Spring MVC equivalents\" as in_progress.\n\n**This Session's Work:**\n\n1. **Reading JSF Web Bean Files** - Read all 11 JSF files that needed migration:\n   - Booking.java (@FlowScoped), Track.java (@ViewScoped), ListCargo.java (@RequestScoped), CargoDetails.java (@RequestScoped), ItinerarySelection.java (@ViewScoped), ChangeDestination.java (@ViewScoped), ChangeDestinationDialog.java (@SessionScoped), ChangeArrivalDeadline.java (@ViewScoped), ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java (@SessionScoped)\n   - EventLogger.java (@ViewScoped, uses PrimeFaces, io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort)\n   - FacesConfiguration.java (@FacesConfig)\n\n2. **Reading Batch Processing Files** - Read 5 batch files + 2 support files:\n   - UploadDirectoryScanner.java (io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled, jakarta.batch)\n   - EventItemReader.java (extends AbstractItemReader)\n   - EventItemWriter.java (extends AbstractItemWriter)\n   - FileProcessorJobListener.java (implements JobListener)\n   - LineParseExceptionListener.java (implements SkipReadListener)\n   - EventFilesCheckpoint.java (POJO, no changes needed)\n   - EventLineParseException.java (POJO, no changes needed)\n   - DateConverter.java (utility, no changes needed)\n\n3. **Launched 3 parallel Task agents:**\n   - Agent 1: Rewrote JSF booking web beans → single BookingController.java REST controller, deleted 9 old JSF files\n   - Agent 2: Rewrote EventLogger.java → Spring REST controller, deleted FacesConfiguration.java\n   - Agent 3: Rewrote 5 batch files for Spring Batch, created BatchJobConfig.java, deleted batch XML/JSF XML files\n\n4. **Fixed remaining public tracking Track.java** - Found via grep that `interfaces/tracking/web/Track.java` still had @ViewScoped. Rewrote it as a Spring REST controller.\n\n5. **Verified no more Quarkus/JSF imports** - grep confirmed clean.\n\n6. **Updated Dockerfile** - Changed CMD from `mvn quarkus:run` to `java -jar target/cargo-tracker-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar`\n\n7. **Deleted JSF XHTML files** - Removed all XHTML templates, booking flow XML, admin pages, etc.\n\n8. **Created smoke.py** - Smoke test file with 8 tests covering REST endpoints.\n\n9. **First compilation attempt** - SUCCESS locally with `mvn clean compile`\n\n10. **First Docker build attempt** - FAILED due to JAXB annotations:\n    - TransitPath.java, TransitPaths.java, HandlingReport.java all used `jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement`\n    - Fixed by removing the JAXB imports and annotations (Jackson doesn't need them)\n\n11. **Second compilation** - SUCCESS\n\n12. **Second Docker build** - FAILED due to test source files still having Quarkus imports:\n    - BookingServiceTest.java (@QuarkusTest, io.quarkus.test.junit, @Inject, jakarta.transaction.Transactional)\n    - BookingServiceTestDataGenerator.java (io.quarkus.runtime.Startup, @ApplicationScoped, @Inject)\n    - TestDataGenerator.java (@ApplicationScoped, @Inject, jakarta.transaction.Transactional)\n    - Fixed by rewriting all 3 test files to Spring Boot equivalents\n\n13. **Third Docker build** - SUCCESS\n\n14. **First container run** - FAILED at startup:\n    - Error: `Table \"APPLICATIONSETTINGS\" not found` when running import.sql\n    - import.sql had `INSERT INTO ApplicationSettings` but table wasn't created yet\n    - Fixed by:\n      - Changed `spring.sql.init.mode=always` to `spring.sql.init.mode=never`\n      - Changed H2 from file-based to in-memory: `jdbc:h2:mem:cargo-tracker-database;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE`\n      - Modified InitLoader.isSampleLoaded() to create ApplicationSettings row if null\n      - Added setId()/getId() methods to ApplicationSettings entity\n      - Set show-sql to false\n\n15. **Fourth Docker build + container run** - SUCCESS:\n    - `Started CargoTrackerApplication in 7.931 seconds`\n\n16. **Smoke tests** - 7 of 8 PASS, 1 FAIL:\n    - PASS: List Locations (13), List Cargos, List Tracking IDs (4), Event Logger Tracking IDs (2), Event Logger Locations (13), Event Logger Voyages (5), Event Types (5)\n    - FAIL: Graph Traversal - returns `{\"transitPaths\":[...]}` (wrapper object) but test expects a raw list\n    - Was about to fix the smoke test when summary was requested\n\n**Files Modified in This Session:**\n\n1. BookingController.java (NEW) - replaces 9 JSF beans\n2. EventLogger.java (REWRITTEN) - JSF → REST controller\n3. FacesConfiguration.java (DELETED)\n4. Track.java (interfaces/tracking/web/) (REWRITTEN) - JSF → REST controller\n5. UploadDirectoryScanner.java (REWRITTEN) - Quarkus scheduler → Spring @Scheduled\n6. EventItemReader.java (REWRITTEN) - Jakarta Batch → Spring Batch ItemReader\n7. EventItemWriter.java (REWRITTEN) - Jakarta Batch → Spring Batch ItemWriter\n8. FileProcessorJobListener.java (REWRITTEN) - Jakarta Batch → Spring Batch\n9. LineParseExceptionListener.java (REWRITTEN) - Jakarta Batch → Spring Batch\n10. BatchJobConfig.java (NEW) - Spring Batch job configuration\n11. TransitPath.java - removed @XmlRootElement\n12. TransitPaths.java - removed @XmlRootElement\n13. HandlingReport.java - removed @XmlRootElement\n14. Dockerfile - CMD changed to Spring Boot\n15. application.properties - SQL init and H2 changes\n16. InitLoader.java - handle missing ApplicationSettings\n17. ApplicationSettings.java - added setId()/getId()\n18. BookingServiceTest.java (test) - Quarkus → Spring Boot\n19. BookingServiceTestDataGenerator.java (test) - Quarkus → Spring Boot\n20. TestDataGenerator.java (test) - Quarkus → Spring Boot\n21. smoke.py (NEW) - smoke tests\n22. Multiple XHTML/XML files (DELETED)\n\n**Pending Tasks:**\n- Fix the Graph Traversal smoke test (expects list, gets dict with transitPaths)\n- Create CHANGELOG.md\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user is an autonomous AI coding agent tasked with migrating a complete Java Cargo Tracker DDD application from **Quarkus** to **Spring Boot**. The migration must be completed in a single execution without requesting additional input. The application is located at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_1/output`.\n   \n   Key requirements:\n   - Migrate all framework-specific dependencies, annotations, and patterns from Quarkus to Spring Boot\n   - Generate smoke tests to verify functionality\n   - Build as Docker image, run container, execute smoke tests\n   - Use `$SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME` (=`my_test_container_1`), `$SCARF_IMAGE_TAG` (=`my_test_image_1`) for Docker operations with `-p 0:8080`\n   - Document all actions in `CHANGELOG.md`\n   - Address any errors and iterate until the application builds, runs, and passes tests\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Quarkus → Spring Boot 3.4.3** framework migration (Java 21)\n   - **DDD (Domain-Driven Design)** architecture with aggregates, repositories, services, value objects\n   - **CDI → Spring DI**: `@ApplicationScoped`→`@Service/@Component/@Repository`, `@Inject`→`@Autowired`, `@ConfigProperty`→`@Value`\n   - **Quarkus Panache → Standard JPA** EntityManager-based repositories\n   - **JAX-RS → Spring MVC**: `@Path`→`@RequestMapping`, `@GET`→`@GetMapping`, `@POST`→`@PostMapping`\n   - **JSF/PrimeFaces → Spring REST controllers** (JSF not supported in Spring Boot)\n   - **Jakarta Batch (JBeret) → Spring Batch**: `AbstractItemReader`→`ItemReader`, `AbstractItemWriter`→`ItemWriter`, XML job descriptor → Java `@Configuration`\n   - **Quarkus Scheduler → Spring @Scheduled**: `@Scheduled(every=\"2m\")`→`@Scheduled(fixedRate=120000)`\n   - **CDI Events → Spring ApplicationEventPublisher**\n   - **JAX-RS SSE → Spring SseEmitter**\n   - **Manual JMS consumers → @JmsListener**\n   - **ActiveMQ Artemis** as JMS broker (AMQP → TCP/core protocol)\n   - **H2 in-memory database** (changed from file-based during debugging)\n   - **JAXB annotations removed** (not needed with Jackson JSON)\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   **NEW FILES CREATED IN THIS SESSION:**\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/BookingController.java`** (NEW)\n     - Consolidates all 9 JSF booking web beans into a single Spring REST controller\n     - Endpoints: `/rest/booking/locations`, `/rest/booking/cargo`, `/rest/booking/cargos`, `/rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}`, `/rest/booking/tracking/ids`, `/rest/booking/tracking/{trackingId}`, `/rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/routes`, `/rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/assign-route`, `/rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/destination`, `/rest/booking/cargo/{trackingId}/deadline`\n     - Written by Task agent; old JSF files (Booking.java, Track.java, ListCargo.java, CargoDetails.java, ItinerarySelection.java, ChangeDestination.java, ChangeDestinationDialog.java, ChangeArrivalDeadline.java, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java) were deleted\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/BatchJobConfig.java`** (NEW)\n     - Spring Batch `@Configuration` class replacing the XML job descriptor\n     - Defines `eventFilesProcessorJob` and `eventProcessingStep` beans with chunk-oriented processing\n\n   - **`smoke.py`** (NEW)\n     - 8 smoke tests: List Locations, List Cargos, List Tracking IDs, Graph Traversal, Event Logger Tracking IDs/Locations/Voyages, Event Types\n     - Uses `urllib.request` for HTTP calls, accepts base URL as CLI argument\n\n   **FILES REWRITTEN IN THIS SESSION:**\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/Track.java`**\n     - Changed from JSF `@ViewScoped` `@Named(\"publicTrack\")` bean to Spring `@RestController`\n     - Important because it was missed by the Task agents and found via grep\n     ```java\n     @RestController\n     @RequestMapping(\"/rest/public/track\")\n     public class Track {\n         @Autowired private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n         @Autowired private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n         @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}\")\n         public ResponseEntity<CargoTrackingViewAdapter> trackById(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n             // ... finds cargo and returns adapter or 404\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/mobile/EventLogger.java`**\n     - Changed from JSF `@ViewScoped` to Spring `@RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/event-logger\")`\n     - Removed PrimeFaces, FacesContext, SelectItem, `io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort` imports\n     - Written by Task agent\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/UploadDirectoryScanner.java`**\n     - Changed from `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled` + `jakarta.batch.runtime.BatchRuntime` to Spring `@Scheduled(fixedRate=120000)` + `JobLauncher`\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/EventItemReader.java`**\n     - Changed from `extends AbstractItemReader` (Jakarta Batch) to `implements ItemReader<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt>` (Spring Batch)\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/EventItemWriter.java`**\n     - Changed from `extends AbstractItemWriter` to `implements ItemWriter<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt>` with `write(Chunk<?>)`\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/FileProcessorJobListener.java`**\n     - Changed from `implements JobListener` (Jakarta Batch) to `implements JobExecutionListener` (Spring Batch)\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/LineParseExceptionListener.java`**\n     - Changed from `implements SkipReadListener` (Jakarta Batch) to `implements SkipListener<...>` (Spring Batch)\n\n   **FILES EDITED IN THIS SESSION:**\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/TransitPath.java`**\n     - Removed `import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;` and `@XmlRootElement` annotation\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/TransitPaths.java`**\n     - Removed `import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;` and `@XmlRootElement` annotation\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/rest/HandlingReport.java`**\n     - Removed `import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;` and `@XmlRootElement` annotation\n\n   - **`Dockerfile`**\n     - Changed line 41 from: `CMD /var/lib/artemis-broker/bin/artemis-service start && mvn quarkus:run`\n     - To: `CMD /var/lib/artemis-broker/bin/artemis-service start && java -jar target/cargo-tracker-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar`\n\n   - **`src/main/resources/application.properties`**\n     - Changed datasource URL from `jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-data/cargo-tracker-database` to `jdbc:h2:mem:cargo-tracker-database;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE`\n     - Changed `spring.jpa.show-sql=true` to `spring.jpa.show-sql=false`\n     - Changed `spring.sql.init.mode=always` to `spring.sql.init.mode=never`\n     - Removed `spring.sql.init.data-locations=classpath:import.sql`\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/InitLoader.java`**\n     - Modified `isSampleLoaded()` to create ApplicationSettings row if it doesn't exist:\n     ```java\n     if (settings == null) {\n         settings = new ApplicationSettings();\n         settings.setId(1L);\n         settings.setSampleLoaded(true);\n         entityManager.persist(settings);\n         return false;\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java`**\n     - Added `getId()` and `setId(Long id)` methods\n\n   - **`src/test/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingServiceTest.java`**\n     - Changed from `@QuarkusTest` + `@Inject` + `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` to `@SpringBootTest` + `@Autowired` + `org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional`\n\n   - **`src/test/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingServiceTestDataGenerator.java`**\n     - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped @Startup @Inject @PostConstruct` to `@Component @Autowired @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)`\n\n   - **`src/test/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/TestDataGenerator.java`**\n     - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped @Inject @Transactional(jakarta.transaction)` to `@Service @PersistenceContext @Transactional(Spring)`\n\n   **FILES DELETED:**\n   - 9 JSF booking web beans (Booking.java, Track.java, ListCargo.java, etc.)\n   - FacesConfiguration.java\n   - META-INF/faces-config.xml, META-INF/web.xml, META-INF/batch-jobs/EventFilesProcessorJob.xml\n   - All XHTML files and JSF template directories under META-INF/resources/\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   \n   - **JAXB XmlRootElement compilation error** (first `mvn clean compile`):\n     - 3 files used `jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement` which isn't in Spring Boot dependencies\n     - Fixed by removing the JAXB import and `@XmlRootElement` annotation from TransitPath.java, TransitPaths.java, HandlingReport.java\n\n   - **Quarkus imports in test source files** (Docker build with `mvn clean install -DskipTests`):\n     - `-DskipTests` skips test execution but NOT test compilation\n     - BookingServiceTest.java had `io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest`, BookingServiceTestDataGenerator.java had `io.quarkus.runtime.Startup`, TestDataGenerator.java had `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped`\n     - Fixed by rewriting all 3 test files with Spring Boot equivalents (@SpringBootTest, @Autowired, @Component, @Service, Spring @Transactional)\n\n   - **ApplicationSettings table not found at startup** (first container run):\n     - `import.sql` had `INSERT INTO ApplicationSettings` but ran before JPA DDL schema creation despite `spring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true`\n     - Fixed by: (1) setting `spring.sql.init.mode=never` to disable import.sql, (2) switching to in-memory H2, (3) modifying InitLoader to create the ApplicationSettings row programmatically if it doesn't exist\n\n   - **Smoke test Graph Traversal failure**:\n     - Endpoint returns `{\"transitPaths\":[...]}` (wrapper object) but test asserts `isinstance(data, list)`\n     - **NOT YET FIXED** - was about to fix when summary was requested\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully migrated all JSF web beans by consolidating into REST controllers\n   - Successfully migrated Jakarta Batch to Spring Batch with proper configuration\n   - Resolved H2 database initialization ordering issue by switching to programmatic data loading\n   - Application starts successfully in Docker with sample data loaded\n   - 7 of 8 smoke tests pass; 1 test needs minor fix (assertion type check)\n\n6. All User Messages:\n   - **Message 1** (from previous session, summarized): Full migration specification with detailed checklist, environment constraints, Docker isolation requirements, migration workflow, validation protocol, error handling instructions. Key: \"Begin migration now.\"\n   - **Message 2** (this session): \"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context.\" followed by a detailed summary of the previous session's work. Instruction: \"Please continue the conversation from where we left it off without asking the user any further questions. Continue with the last task that you were asked to work on.\"\n   - **Message 3** (system reminder about TodoWrite - not explicit user message)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Fix the Graph Traversal smoke test (change assertion from `isinstance(data, list)` to handle dict with `transitPaths` key)\n   - Re-run smoke tests to confirm all 8 pass\n   - Create `CHANGELOG.md` documenting all migration changes\n   - Clean up the container after tests\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The application is running in Docker container `my_test_container_1` on port 33936. Smoke tests were just executed with 7/8 passing. The one failing test is `test_graph_traversal()` in `smoke.py` which asserts `isinstance(data, list)` but the `/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path` endpoint returns a JSON object `{\"transitPaths\":[...]}`. The curl output confirms:\n   ```json\n   {\"transitPaths\":[{\"transitEdges\":[{\"voyageNumber\":\"0400S\",\"fromUnLocode\":\"CNHKG\",...}]},...]}\n   ```\n   \n   The smoke test code at issue:\n   ```python\n   def test_graph_traversal():\n       status, body = http_get(\"/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path?origin=CNHKG&destination=FIHEL\")\n       assert status == 200, f\"Expected 200, got {status}: {body}\"\n       data = json.loads(body)\n       assert isinstance(data, list), f\"Expected list, got {type(data)}\"\n   ```\n   \n   I was reading the smoke test file to locate the exact line to fix when the summary was requested.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Fix the `test_graph_traversal` function in `smoke.py` to handle the wrapper object format (check for `data[\"transitPaths\"]` being a list instead of `data` being a list), then re-run smoke tests to verify all 8 pass. After that, create `CHANGELOG.md`. The smoke test file does NOT need a Docker rebuild - it can be run from the host. But if a rebuild is needed for other reasons, rebuild the image first. The container is currently running and accessible at `http://localhost:33936/cargo-tracker`..\nPlease continue the conversation from where we left it off without asking the user any further questions. Continue with the last task that you were asked to work on."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8543075e-efdd-4cb8-9429-6656037679ab","uuid":"d93338d1-d29b-40b9-8403-63370ff8f445","isSynthetic":true}
